                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.11/3696: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_apparent-typo-based-on-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-05T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1291—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Your 10 March 29 3 p.m.</p>
                <p>Inform Dr. Nansen that this Government would greatly appreciate his further
                    efforts in this matter. You may invite his attention to the Secretary’s
                    statement of March 25th regarding trade with Russia,<note n="98"
                        xml:id="d749fn98">See telegram Mar. 25, to the consul at Reval, <ref
                            target="#pg_768">p. 768</ref>.</note> copy of which was handed to
                    Litvinoff by the Consul at Reval. Department assumes this has been published in
                    full in Christiania.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
